net.sf.mmm.util.query.base.expression

Class SqlOperator<T,S>

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sf.mmm.util.query.base.expression.SqlOperator<T,S>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the generic type of the comparison type.
    S - the generic type of the second comparison argument - typically same as first (<T>).
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    SqlOperator.SqlOperatorBetween, SqlOperator.SqlOperatorContainment, SqlOperator.SqlOperatorEmptyness, SqlOperator.SqlOperatorNumber, SqlOperator.SqlOperatorString

    public abstract class SqlOperator<T,S>
extends Object
    A SqlOperator represents the SQL function that compares two given values in expressions (e.g. in where clauses).
    Since:
    8.0.0
    Author:
    hohwille
